<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06019139 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06019139 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  RACIAL; DISCRIMINATION; LAWSUIT; FINE; HOUSING; LOST  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  The house where white supremacist Tom Metzger lives and spreads his ideascould soon be up for sale to collect some of the $12.5 million in damages wonin a lawsuit.;    But after a court official Thursday attached to Metzger'sfence the notice of a hearing on the pending sale, the 53-year-old TVrepairman vowed to fight it.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  California News  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  SUPREMACIST MAY LOSE HOME TO PAY PLAINTIFF  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     &quot;I'll fight 'em all and I'll keep on fighting,&quot; Metzer said.;    InOctober, an Oregon jury returned the damages award to the family of MulugetaSeraw, an Ethiopian national. The jury found Metzger incited racist&quot;skinheads&quot; to fatally beat Seraw on a Portland street.;    Metzger is founderand leader of the White Aryan Resistance, or WAR.;    The notice posted onMetzger's home announced a Feb. 21 hearing for Metzger to give a reason whyhis house shouldn't be sold.;    Efforts are also under way to track $170,000Metzger allegedly deposited last year in a WAR bank account.;    Metzger, aformer California leader of the Ku Klux Klan who acts as his own attorney, iswatching his legal problems mount.;    He also has been called to testifybefore a federal grand jury investigating last year's bombing of the U.S.Courthouse in San Diego. No one was injured, but the blast damaged thecourthouse doors.;    Metzger has been ordered to submit a list of hisnewspaper's subscribers, but says he'll refuse.;    &quot;I'll probably be held incontempt and have to go to jail for not giving it to them,&quot; he said Thursday.;   Metzger's home is his major asset. It's also the site of his repair shopand where he publishes WAR literature. The house's value is estimated atanywhere from $60,000 to $145,000.;    State law says the first $45,000 ofequity from the sale goes to Metzger and his wife, Kathleen.;    AttorneyJames McElroy, who is working to help seize Metzger's assets, said theunderlying purpose was to stop Metzger from promoting racist ideas throughWAR, which has been recruiting young skinheads nationwide.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Fallbrook  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910119  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Saturday  </DAY><MONTH>  January  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  331  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Saturday January 19, 199100019139,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>